parameters.name: BR
parameters.description:
The radial component (R) points from the Sun to the spacecraft,         
      positive away from the Sun.

parameters.name: BT
parameters.description:
RTN tangetial (T) component of the magnetic field in nT. T is parallel  
      to the Solar Equatorial plane (Omega[Sun] x R).

parameters.name: BPHI
parameters.description:
RTN normal (N) component of the magnetic field in nT. N completes the   
      right handed set, and is roughly normal to the Solar Equatorial plane.

parameters.name: BTOTAL
parameters.description: Average of the magnetic field magnitudes in nT.

parameters.name: RANGE
parameters.description: Sun to spacecraft range in units of AU (1 AU = 149674000 km).

parameters.name: LATITUDE
parameters.description: Solar heliocentric latitude of the spacecraft in degrees.

parameters.name: LONGITUDE
parameters.description:
Solar longitude of the spacecraft measured in degrees East of the       
      Sun-Aries line.

parameters.name: X_IHG
parameters.description:
Inertial Heliographic Cartesian X component (along the Sun-Aries line,  
      positive towards Aries) of the spacecraft position in AU.

parameters.name: Y_IHG
parameters.description:
Inertial Heliographic Cartesian Y component (completes the right handed 
      set, Z x X) of the spacecraft position in AU.

parameters.name: Z_IHG
parameters.description:
Inertial Heliographic Cartesian Z component (Omega[Sun], positive in    
      direction of angular momentum) of the spacecraft position in AU.

parameters.name: NPTS
parameters.description: Number of points in the average.
